<Layout title="Disclaimer and Terms of Use" description="How to use this reference and its templates: educational information only, not legal or compliance advice, provided without warranty. Independent and not affiliated with any regulator or standards body.">
  <header class="dc-hero">
    <div class="wrap dc-inner">
      <nav class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> <span>›</span> Disclaimer and Terms</nav>
      <h1 class="dc-h1">Disclaimer and Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="dc-lead">Please read this before you use the articles and templates on this site. Using the site means you accept these terms.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="wrap dc-body">
    <section>
      <h2>Educational information, not advice</h2>
      <p>This site is a free, independent educational reference on quality systems, data integrity, and validation in regulated life sciences. Everything on it, including articles, templates, and checklists, is general information for learning and as a starting point. It is not legal, regulatory, compliance, medical, or other professional advice, and it does not create any professional relationship. Decisions about your products, processes, and compliance should be made with your own qualified personnel and, where appropriate, your own legal and regulatory advisers. Reading an article or copying a template does not create a consulting, advisory, fiduciary, or other professional relationship, and confers no rights associated with one.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>No warranty, verify against the official source</h2>
      <p>The content is provided "as is," without warranty of any kind, express or implied, including accuracy, completeness, or fitness for a particular purpose. Regulations, guidances, and standards change, and interpretations differ. Always confirm any regulation, guidance, standard, citation, date, or technical detail against the current, official, published source, and against your own quality system, before you rely on it. Do not act on this site alone.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>How this content is prepared, including AI assistance</h2>
      <p>This material is researched and drafted by the author with the assistance of AI tools, and then reviewed. AI-assisted text can contain errors, including a misstated requirement, an out-of-date position, or an incorrect citation. Treat everything here as a starting point, not a primary source. Confirm every regulation, guidance, standard, clause, date, figure, and citation against the current official published source, and apply your own professional judgment, before you act on it.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Limitation of liability, errors, and use at your own risk</h2>
      <p>Everything on this site is provided "as is" and "as available," without warranties of any kind, express or implied, including any implied warranty of merchantability, fitness for a particular regulatory or compliance purpose, accuracy, or completeness. To the fullest extent permitted by law, the author is not liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, consequential, special, or punitive damages, or for any regulatory outcome, inspection finding, fine, batch rejection, recall, business loss, or other consequence, arising from use of or reliance on this site, its content, or its documents, even if advised of the possibility. The content may contain errors or omissions or become outdated as regulations and guidance change. You assume full responsibility and risk for evaluating the information and for any use of the templates within your own systems and processes.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Using the templates and documents</h2>
      <p>The templates are generic starting points written in original wording and presented on the page for you to read and copy. They are not a finished compliance solution. You are responsible for adapting each one to your own company, system, and process, completing every placeholder, having it reviewed and approved through your own document control, validating its use where required, and ensuring it meets the regulations that apply to you. Copying or using a template does not create, prove, or guarantee compliance.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Independence</h2>
      <p>This site is independent and personal. It is not affiliated with, endorsed by, sponsored by, or representing the FDA, EMA, MHRA, PIC/S, ISPE, PDA, USP, ISO, IEC, ICH, ASTM, any other regulator or standards body, or any employer. Any views are the author's own.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Citations, trademarks, and copyright</h2>
      <p>Regulations, guidances, and standards are referred to by their number, title, and publisher for identification and educational purposes only. Trademarks, product names, and standard names are the property of their respective owners and are used nominatively, with no claim of ownership or endorsement. For example, GAMP is a registered trademark of ISPE; references to GAMP, ISPE, and similar marks are nominative, identify the referenced work only, and do not imply affiliation, sponsorship, certification, or endorsement.</p>
      <p>Where regulatory text is quoted, it is quoted briefly and attributed, and is drawn from public sources such as the US Code of Federal Regulations and FDA guidance (US government works) and EU legislation. The site does not reproduce the copyrighted text of standards published by bodies such as ISO, IEC, USP, ISPE, or ASTM; those are described in original wording and referenced by citation only. To obtain the full text of any standard, purchase or access it from the publisher. Any brief quotation of third-party material is for commentary, criticism, teaching, and education, consistent with the fair-use principles of Section 107 of the US Copyright Act. If you believe any material infringes a copyright, email the address below with the URL, a description of the work, and the basis of your claim, and it will be reviewed and removed or revised where appropriate.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Independently developed, original, non-confidential content</h2>
      <p>All content, including the articles and templates, is independently developed educational material based on publicly available information and general professional knowledge. It does not contain, and is not derived from, any confidential, proprietary, or trade secret information, internal procedure, document, dataset, template, risk methodology, or governance framework of any current or former employer, client, or other third party. All company names, systems, numbers, and examples are generic or fictional and are used only to illustrate a general principle. The views are the author's own and do not represent any employer, past or present.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Privacy</h2>
      <p>This is a static informational site. It does not require an account or login, it does not host contact or signup forms, and it does not set advertising or tracking cookies. It does not ask for or collect personal information from visitors. If you choose to email the address below, your message and email address are used only to respond to you. Basic aggregate traffic and security data may be processed by the site's hosting and content-delivery provider to operate and protect the site, governed by that provider's own terms.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Acceptance, changes, and governing law</h2>
      <p>By accessing or using this site you accept these terms. If you do not agree with them, do not use the site. These terms may be updated at any time without notice, and the version posted here governs your use. To the extent any dispute arises out of or relates to the site or its content, it is governed by the laws of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts, United States, without regard to its conflict-of-laws rules.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>License and permitted use</h2>
      <p>Copyright © 2026 madhadi.com. All rights reserved. The articles and templates are free to read, with no paywall and no login. You may copy and adapt the templates for your own internal business use, including completing them and routing them through your own document control. You may not republish, redistribute, resell, sublicense, mirror, or post the articles, the templates, or the collection elsewhere, in whole or in substantial part, with or without modification, without prior written permission. Brief excerpts may be quoted with attribution and a link. This permission is granted to you for your own use only, is revocable, and may be changed or withdrawn at any time.</p>
